extends layout

block content
  .container
    .page-header
      h1 Privacy Policy
      p Last updated: April 7, 2026

    .legal-content
      section
        h2 1. Introduction
        p
          | Error Handling Helpline ("Company", "we", "our", or "us") operates the website 
          | (the "Site"). This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, 
          | and disclosure of personal data when you use our Service and the choices you have 
          | associated with that data.

      section
        h2 2. Information Collection and Use
        p We collect several different types of information for various purposes:

        h3 2.1 Personal Data
        ul
          li Email address
          li First name and last name
          li Username
          li Password (hashed and encrypted)
          li Phone number (optional)
          li Address, State, Province, ZIP/Postal code, City (optional)
          li Cookies and Usage Data

        h3 2.2 Usage Data
        p
          | When you access the Service, we may automatically collect certain information 
          | about your device, such as:
        ul
          li Your IP address
          li Browser type and version
          li Pages you visit
          li Time and date of your visit
          li Time spent on pages
          li Device identifiers

      section
        h2 3. Use of Data
        p Error Handling Helpline uses the collected data for various purposes:
        ul
          li To provide and maintain our Service
          li To notify you about changes to our Service
          li To allow you to participate in interactive features of our Service
          li To provide customer support
          li To gather analysis or valuable information
          li To monitor the usage of our Service
          li To detect, prevent and address technical issues

      section
        h2 4. Security of Data
        p
          | The security of your data is important to us, but remember that no method of 
          | transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure. 
          | While we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your Personal Data, 
          | we cannot guarantee its absolute security.

      section
        h2 5. Cookies
        p
          | We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to track activity on our Service 
          | and hold certain information. You can instruct your browser to refuse all cookies or 
          | to indicate when a cookie is being sent. However, if you do not accept cookies, you 
          | may not be able to use some portions of our Service.

      section
        h2 6. Third-Party Services
        p
          | Our Service may contain links to other sites that are not operated by us. If you click 
          | on a third party link, you will be directed to that third party's site. We strongly 
          | advise you to review the Privacy Policy of every site you visit.

      section
        h2 7. OAuth Integration
        p
          | We allow you to sign up and log in using GitHub and Google accounts. When you choose 
          | to use these services, we receive limited information from these providers including 
          | your email address and profile information. This is used solely to create and maintain 
          | your account with us.

      section
        h2 8. Children's Privacy
        p
          | Our Service does not address anyone under the age of 18 ("Children"). We do not 
          | knowingly collect personally identifiable information from anyone under the age of 18. 
          | If you are a parent or guardian and you are aware that your child has provided us with 
          | Personal Data, please contact us immediately.

      section
        h2 9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
        p
          | We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes 
          | by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last updated" date at 
          | the top of this Privacy Policy.

      section
        h2 10. Contact Us
        p
          | If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
        ul
          li By email: privacy@errorhandlinghelpline.com
          li By mail: 
            | Error Handling Helpline, [Your Address], [City], [State] [ZIP Code]

    .legal-footer
      a.btn.btn-secondary(href="/") Back to Home
